# Discord bot configuration token
DISCORD_TOKEN=
# Optional: path to audio file (defaults to audio/clip.mp3)
AUDIO_PATH=audio/audio.mp3
# Optional: ID of the user that should trigger the bot when they join a voice channel
# If empty, bot reacts to any non-bot user joining.
#TARGET_USER_ID=123456789012345678
## Example: set to numeric Discord user ID to trigger only that user
#TARGET_USER_ID=123456789012345678
# Or instead you can specify a username or username#discriminator
## To allow multiple users, set a comma-separated list in `TARGET_USERS`.
## Each item can be a numeric ID, a username, or username#discriminator.
## Examples:
#TARGET_USERS=123456789012345678
#TARGET_USERS=adi,otherUser,alice#1234
## (If `TARGET_USERS` is empty, bot will react to any non-bot user.)